2) You can specify `fromActionState` and `endActionState` when fetching actions, so if you specify both to be consecutive action states for the specific action, you can fetch it. The "ID" would be the `fromActionState`
```
reducer.fetchActions({
  fromActionState: id,
  endActionState: hash([id, actionHash])
})
```

3) I think actions have the exact order and can't be processed in a different order because the final actionState wouldn't match.
